<TITLE> AL envisions S Asian anti-terror taskforce </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 12 (bdnews24.com) - Awami League in its manifesto has promised to set up a taskforce to combat terrorism and militancy in the South Asian region, in the backdrop of the Mumbai terror attacks. "A South Asian Task Force will be formed for meeting the challenges of terrorism and militancy," the 23-point manifesto reads. AL president Sheikh Hasina on Friday morning rolled out party's 'Charter for Change' ahead of the ninth national election at the Dhaka Sheraton. The last point of the 23-point manifesto, which addressed foreign policy, said: "Bangladesh will take an active role in the preservation of world peace." "An independent foreign policy will be pursued in adherence to the principles of 'Friendship with all and malice towards none'." "Friendly relationship will be maintained with India, Nepal, Bhutan and Myanmar, our neighbouring countries, in the context of further strengthening cooperation with all." "Regional and sub-regional cooperation will be further strengthened including relationship with the member countries of SAARC, BIMSTEC and D-8," it reads. The party manifesto said, "Development cooperation will be deepened and expanded with the developed countries including USA, European Union, Japan and Canada." "Friendly relations will be strengthened with Russia, China and the member states of ASEAN." bdnews
